Tube missing. Opercular peduncle smooth, white. Operculum funnel with 23 radii with pointed tips (
Fig. 4I
); verticil with seven yellowish spines, curving abruptly inwards, forming an external knob (
Fig. 4I
); all spines similar in shape and size, with pointed tips; with basal internal spinule and two welldeveloped lateral spinules in middle position, without external spinules, wings or central tooth (
Fig. 4I
). Special collar chaetae with two pointed, short teeth and smooth distal blade.

Intertidal to 

41 m
.

On mangrove roots, bryozoans, seagrasses and algae, sea urchin spines, gastropod shells, sponges, corals (

Orbicella annularis

), calcareous rocks and on artificial substrates such as fouling on wood dock pilings (
Díaz 1994
; 
Bastida-Zavala & Salazar-Vallejo 2000b
; 
Bastida-Zavala & ten Hove 2002
).
